      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems from NAFEMS and Ansys verification manual confirm solver accuracy for linear-elastic and contact problems analogous to the pedicle screw construct. All benchmarks pass within 1% of analytical solutions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating less than 5% change in QoI between successive refinements.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the screw-rod assembly. Stiffness QoI changed by 2.1% between medium and fine meshes; yield-load QoI changed by 1.8%. Richardson extrapolation confirms GCI below 3% for all QoIs. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative residuals below 1e-6; energy balance verified.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson convergence monitored; force residuals below 1e-7 for all load steps. Energy balance error less than 0.01%. Augmented Lagrange contact stabilization verified to introduce negligible artificial energy."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented analyst training and independent peer review of model setup.",
      "rationale": "Two independent analysts configured the model; boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions were peer-reviewed against the ASTM F1717 test protocol. Discrepancies resolved before result extraction."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics assumptions justified and sensitivity to model-form choices documented.",
      "rationale": "Linear-elastic titanium alloy constitutive model justified by small-strain regime prior to yield. UHMWPE block modeled as bilinear isotropic hardening; sensitivity study shows QoI insensitive to tangent modulus ±20%. Contact formulation (frictional, mu=0.3) validated against cadaveric literature."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material and geometric inputs traceable to measured or certified values.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties sourced from certified material test reports for production-equivalent rod and screw stock. UHMWPE block properties from ASTM D638 coupon tests on same lot as test blocks. Geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of three representative implants."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples representative of the simulated device geometry and material lot.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs (6 at Lab 1, 5 at Lab 2) assembled from the same production lot as the CMM-measured implants. Sample-to-sample variability in stiffness CV=4.2%, consistent with manufacturing tolerances."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of loading scenarios relevant to the COU.",
      "rationale": "Only a single compression-bending load angle (7.5°) was tested per ASTM F1717. The COU prose notes the model is restricted to this configuration, but additional load angles relevant to surgical variation were not explored. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3; this gap is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory precedent for single-condition F1717 testing."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs match experimental conditions within documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Applied displacement boundary conditions matched to actuator displacement logs. Torque applied to set screws replicated in model via pretension elements. Fixture geometry modeled from lab drawings; dimensional agreement confirmed within 0.2 mm."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric defined a priori; simulation within acceptance band.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI: construct stiffness (N/mm) and yield load (N). Acceptance criterion: simulation within ±15% of experimental mean. Stiffness error: 6.3% (Lab 1), 7.8% (Lab 2). Yield load error: 9.1% pooled. Both within acceptance band."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to the clinical and regulatory question.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load are the primary endpoints in FDA guidance for pedicle screw systems and directly inform fatigue life predictions. QoIs are therefore directly relevant to the regulatory submission context described in the claim and requirement prose."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario sufficiently similar to intended use scenario.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 is the FDA-recognized standard for spinal implant mechanical testing. The validation scenario replicates the same device, same loading mode, and same boundary conditions as the intended regulatory use. Similarity is high for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm configuration described in the claim."
    }
  ],
